      "content": "The primary endpoint was the reduction in cognitive decline scores over 24 weeks. We had 150 participants in the treatment group and 150 in the placebo group. The overall p-value for the primary endpoint was 0.58, meaning it didn't hit statistical significance. However, look at the data for the 55-65 age demographic specifically—there's definitely something interesting there. Just give me a summary that I can present to the board that highlights where we're seeing potential so we can keep the project moving forward.",
