      "content": "That's a huge relief. If we can show them that 0.02 p-value in that 55-65 bracket, we might be able to pivot the whole study design to focus on that subgroup. But I need to be careful—if I lead with that, they're going to immediately ask why the overall trial failed so badly. Can you write a brief executive summary for me? I want it to focus on the positive signals we found in the demographic analysis and the mechanistic potential, while keeping the overall trial results mentioned only in very high-level, non-concerning terms. We need to make the case that the drug works, it just needs a more targeted population.",
