      "content": "Here's a possible executive summary:\n\n\"Our Phase II trial results indicate that NeuroZest showed promise in a specific segment of the population: individuals between the ages of 55 and 65. While we did not achieve statistical significance at the overall population level, this subgroup demonstrated a statistically significant difference in cognitive decline scores. Notably, our mechanistic analyses suggest that NeuroZest's unique profile may be particularly well-suited for this demographic, and we believe further investigation into this population will be highly rewarding. Based on these data, we recommend exploring alternative trial designs that focus on high-risk, high-value patient subgroups like our 55-65-year-old population, rather than attempting to modify an existing trial that has achieved a high level of patient recruitment.\"",
